<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="27" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d27">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 611.3231/187.</note>
                        <head>[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Petropolis</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-15"><hi rend="italic">January 15,
                                1911</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Executive decree 12th grants tariff reduction during 1911 of 30 per cent,
                            an increase<note n="1" xml:id="d27fn1">In increase of the
                                reduction.</note> on American flour and 20 per cent on remaining 15
                            items so favored during 1910. Have submitted supplemental list, but
                            further concessions this year improbable. Conclusion of a reciprocity
                            may be proposed.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Dudley.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>